{
  "local_port": 46402,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the steps for registering a company in India?",
  "response": "Registering a company in India involves several steps and can be done online through the Ministry of Corporate Affairs (MCA) portal. Below is a step-by-step guide to the process:\n\n---\n\n### **Step 1: Obtain Digital Signature Certificate (DSC)**\n- A DSC is required for filing online forms with the MCA.\n- Apply for a Class 2 or Class 3 DSC from certified agencies like e-Mudhra, NSDL, or others.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 2: Obtain Director Identification Number (DIN)**\n- Every proposed director of the company must have a DIN.\n- Apply for DIN through the MCA portal by filing Form DIR-3.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 3: Reserve the Company Name**\n- Choose a unique name for your company and check its availability on the MCA portal using the **RUN (Reserve Unique Name)** service or **SPICe+** form.\n- Submit up to two preferred names with their significance. The name must comply with the naming guidelines under the Companies Act, 2013.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 4: File SPICe+ Form**\n- SPICe+ (Simplified Proforma for Incorporating Company Electronically Plus) is the main form for company incorporation.\n- Submit SPICe+ (Form INC-32) along with:\n  - Memorandum of Association (MOA) (Form INC-33)\n  - Articles of Association (AOA) (Form INC-34)\n- This form also facilitates PAN, TAN, EPFO, ESIC, and bank account registration.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 5: Apply for PAN and TAN**\n- PAN (Permanent Account Number) and TAN (Tax Deduction and Collection Account Number) are applied for automatically when filing the SPICe+ form.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 6: Pay the Required Fees**\n- Pay the prescribed registration fees and stamp duty (based on the authorized capital and state of incorporation) during the online filing process.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 7: Verification and Approval**\n- The Registrar of Companies (RoC) will verify the submitted documents and forms.\n- If everything is in order, the RoC will issue a **Certificate of Incorporation** (CoI), which includes the Corporate Identity Number (CIN).\n\n---\n\n### **Step 8: Open a Bank Account**\n- After receiving the CoI, open a bank account in the company\u2019s name using the incorporation documents.\n\n---\n\n### **Step 9: Post-Incorporation Compliance**\n- File a declaration of commencement of business (Form INC-20A) within 180 days of incorporation.\n- Maintain proper books of accounts and comply with statutory requirements like audits, annual filings, and GST registration (if applicable).\n\n---\n\n### **Key Documents Required**\n1. Identity and address proof of directors and shareholders.\n2. Proof of registered office address (rent agreement, utility bill, NOC from the owner).\n3. MOA and AOA.\n4. DSC and DIN of directors.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Notes**\n- The entire process usually takes **10-15 days** if all documents are submitted correctly.\n- For **One Person Company (OPC)**, **Private Limited Company**, or **Public Limited Company**, the process is similar, with slight variations in requirements.\n\nFor professional assistance, you can consult a **Chartered Accountant (CA)**, **Company Secretary (CS)**, or **legal advisor**.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
